Content: There is nothing special about this place  We ordered a bunch of tapas Flavours were OK average like the service We had a big table for about 10  12 persons  The waiter was nice but he was not able to manage well the ordering He was keeping forgetting to bring to the table the ordered items Insted of focusing on our table he was talking to his workmates  It is my second time when i stop by this tapas place NOT IMPRESSED

Author: John L.
Content: I have been coming to Cafe Iberico since 1998 and not once have I had a bad experience The food is amazing and what I love about the sangria is that each time I order sangria its unique because the batches marinate for three days from my understanding No two are ever alike

Author: Sharon B.
Content: Went to Cafe Iberico on a recent Sunday night Appreciated that our group of 3 was seated right away but cant say this is the best tapas in Chicago Sorry but the patatas bravas dont even come close to Cafe Babareeba It will probably be a while before I try this place again

Author: Amanda L.
Content: Went here after it was recommended by a friend  Overall it was really good  Our service was EXCEPTIONAL  We had the grilled squid it was AMAZING AMAZING  All of the tapas we ordered were goodWe then went on to order the Paella which I was a little leary about given the cheap 1200 price most resturants it is really expensive  There was enough food for two of us after eating tapas but it wasnt great  If we were to go back again I would not order the Paella and just stick to the tapas  We also only ordered a half carafe of Sangria it was tasty so I would order a full for two people  Other than that I say get there early as the place filled up pretty quick  We will be going back

Author: Mark M.
Content: I was really impressed with the food and service The restaurant was loud and everyone had a great time I was surprised by the affordable prices Good bang for your buck

Author: Mike T.
Content: Ive only been here once late a night to have a few drinks and some dishes to share with my buddyIt was good and Ive been looking to go back with friends to have some tapas

Author: Natalie T.
Content: Went there with a large group on a Saturday night The service was average While the waiter was semiattentive when it was time for entrees to come everyone was handed the wrong order and there were short frenzies of confusion My food was great I shared a shrimp dish with my sister garlicmayonnaise potatoes and a steak  mushroom dishAnd I always love a restaurant where I can buy Sangria by the pitcher I would easily come to this restaurant again maybe next time Ill ditch the group

Author: Ke M.
Content: Went for dinner after work last Friday  The staff was really friendly about changing one of the bar TVs for us to watch a soccer game we wanted to see You cant request a change to the TVs in the dining roomThe food was very tasty and the tapas portions were more generous than I expected  The preparation was heavier than I imagined lots of bread and cream based broths  The sangria was goodWould go back for dinner anytime

Author: eater h.
Content: Am I the only one disliking it I don know where all the great reviews coming from Just want to describe one really awful experience of mineServiceWent there after reading on yelp a girl led us to the table gave us the menu and said she will be right with us After we got the menu I specifically asked for a cup of hot water she said yes and then never came back We sat right next to the cash counter She walks around us all the time and didnt care to ask if we are ready to order or bring the water We had to call another waiter who doesnt speak very fluent Englishlong story short we ordered several tapassmall portion and ended up having a main course for one of them We said we didnt order this one and he said yes you did I told him that I am pretty sure about what I ordered He seemed really pissed took the plate turned his back to me and walked away when I was trying to order sth more I was really unhappyFoodWe didnt order wines so cant comment on that What I can say is that we ordered the signature dishforget its name but it is a big pan of fried rice with some seafood on it which takes 45 mins  It is tastelessIt is just fried rice with some shrimps Everyone can cook it I can be chef for it The other dish we ordered is a pot of broth muscles tasteless as well So disappointing The tapas are okay but I have had better in ChicagoAll in all will never visit again really got my nerves

Author: Jon C.
Content: This is my go to stop before a Cubs day game And everytime theyve won so thats an automatic 1 star  Great selection of Tapas esp the Paella and the bread I wish I remembered everything Ive had here but theres never been one thing I havent enjoyed  Though I cant vouch for the dessert because I dont think Ive ever had enough room  Though I can say the Sangria is great Plus now they recently have half servings which is great if you want to try everything on the menuThough Ive never been their during dinner lunch only Great service great food A must try

Author: Ryan F.
Content: Food was decent and menu was extensive but it was LOUD  I cant think of a restaurant thats been so loud outside of a Chuck E Cheeseand it was a Tuesday night  We first were seated next to a party of 15 that was basically screaming and laughing but saw a table in the corner so moved there  It was only mildly better  The flooring walls and close proximity all make it a loud atmosphere  Bring a large party there but for a date or small group Ba Ba Reeba is a much better option

Author: Ryan H.
Content: Okay so all of the other reviews about this place being loud are accurate  There were probably about 10 empty tables when we were there so about 34 full and it was still quite noisy  While the service was quick and attentive the food was hit and miss  Between my wife my parents and I we ordered about 6 tapas and one dish of paella  The tuna cannelloni was basically tuna salad in a fancy wrap  Other dishes like paella mushrooms queso de cabra olives and vegetables in balsamic oil were tasty but nothing to write home about  The one dish worth noting was the Croquetas de Pollo  If I had to do it over again I would order two or three of this dish  It was excellentBottom line only decent food and dont go here if you get headaches easily

Author: Brooke H.
Content: This was an excellent tapas restaurant Great atmosphere and wonderful food I cant remember the specific names of the dishes but you must get the spicy potatoes and the goat cheese in marinara The saffron scallops were to die for Excellent sangria

Author: Adriana F.
Content: Let me just say I have been going to this place for years birthdays girls night out etcThe tapas here are amazing and at reasonable prices The sangria red is tasty and might I say very potent Also reasonably priced Tapas are meant to be shared with friends and family and that is the type of environment you get in this establishment Staff is friendly and attentive The only set back is the place is not that large and can get packed on the weekends and wait times can be up to 30mins to an hour But order a pitcher of Sangria while you wait

Author: Bec B.
Content: Affordable tapas delicious sangria and chaotic nosy n bustling crowd during the dinner rush  But hey its chicago  where else can you find good tapas at affordable prices

Author: Taylor O.
Content: I had a bright idea walk around starting from the theatre district randomly until I found a Tapas bar  Wouldve been a brighter idea had this not been a date  Somehow managed to not find one for an hour and a half  Finally found a phone book and made our way to Cafe Iberico though nondescript from the front as trendy places tend to be  Couldnt get even a waiting area table for 45 minutes but eventually made our way to a table in the loud busy room  A pitcher of Sangria from a quick and helpful waitress Maria later and we were all good  Spicy potatoes and a plate of steaming veggie paella kicked it a notch or so  We noticed nearly every table had the baked goat cheese so we had to try it  Watching Iron Chef I always wondered how much people were BSing when they spoke of flavors mixing together but I honestly had that thought when I bit in to the warm goat cheese which then slid in to the tomato sauce and the finally the crisp green tinged bread  I shall be ordering that again next time  By the way if you have a cell phone and a bad connection do not scream we are going to a tapas bar so your friends can hear you they might just end up at an entirely different sort of establishment with less goat cheese and more melons

Author: jonah b.
Content: Want to spend roughly 19 per person and have the best night since um the last time you went there Go to Cafe Iberico I love this place I really do Its hip its loud its fun its got Sangria that makes me hallucinate and have the occasional conversation with Moses in the bathroom Iberico is a place to be seen and serves very good tapas aka Spanishstyle appetizers served several at a time Why 19 Well no matter how much you order drinks included the bill always comes out to about 19 per person  youll see Some of the dishes Id recommend garlic mayonnaise potatoes ham puffs my favorite beef tenderloin and spicy red potatoes There is something for everyone including you Aunt Edna on the menu so bring your appetite Just be sure to leave yourself plenty of time when you get there if you have plans later on because the wait can be as long as two hours on any given night Want to hear a secret Go to the bar in the huge dining room to the left after you give your name to the host Its less crowded in there and a much bigger room than the first By the time youre through peoplewatching and exchanging numbers with your future wife the wait will be over Enjoy Oh and congrats on getting those digits buckeroo

Author: Brooke E.
Content: Ive been here 3 times and every time I practically had to be wheel barreled back to the car This place seems to be way crowded and kinda cramped and even though its pretty big you can wind up waiting a long while for a table because they do not take reservations Other then that though I cant recommend this place enough Its the perfect tapas spot in the perfect location The sangria is everything you would expect from a kickass tapas restaurant Im fairly certain Ive had everything on the menu from the todiefor soups to the naughty desert oh yeah ask for the naughty desert youll laugh  its R rated though so dont order it if youre with the childrens The prices are super affordable and the service is superfast and while the hostesses can be a little cranky the servers and bartenders Ive had were all cool and knowledgeable Other then the fact that its LOUD in there its a pretty good spot to hit with friends

Author: Kathleen M.
Content: Absolutely Positively The BEST Tapas Restaurant In the CITY I cannot say enough good things about Iberico Their sangria is wonderful red however is better than white and dirt cheap the place is huge so it doesnt usually take too long to be seated although I would recommend reservations SunThu and the foodoh the food I will preface by saying that I am a slightly picky eater There is nothing on the menu that I wouldnt try I went here once for a holiday party and sampled almost everything on the menu Each dish was more delicious than the last Also you can get a pretty good buzz and have a nice meal for about 20person Go here and you will NOT be disappointed

Author: Shanti N.
Content: Rustic tapas I came here as part of an impromptu after work gathering more in mind of having a glass of sangria than anything else Im not a huge fan of tapas but the pricesportions were reasonable and made it easy to share One major nit I had to pick was the hardness of the bread served with the tomatogoat cheese dip I basically took one bite and that was all I could handle The place was surprisingly packed for midweek and I felt the space could have been somewhat better used as there was basically nothing going on at the front of the restaurant apart from the TVs and a bar More seating could have been placed here to ease the hemmed in feeling of the back roomevent space where we were seated If it is a birthday youre celebrating I believe they also throw in a complimentary dessert Yelp is a family site so I will only go as far as saying that the banana with two scoops of ice cream whipped cream detailing and two candles in the ice cream scoops looked phallic to say the least Not sure if that is the traditional bday dessert presentation or if kitchen staff were feeling extra creative While not a place I would add to my rotation I recommend Cafe Iberico for a lively if not raucous evening

Author: Jessica L.
Content: Fantastic I went there two nights ago with a group of 5 people We had no trouble snagging a table  I only wish it had been bigger to hold all the food We ordered a total of 9 tapas actually we ordered 10 but the waiter must not have heard one of the orders thank goodness to share and most were excellent The baked goat cheese was delicious as were the grilled mixed vegetables the mushrooms and some kind of eggplant bruschetta thingy Garlic shrimp were a little too garlicky for my taste and I wasnt fond of the tails and feet still being on but thats just me Everyone else seemed to love them We also liked the spicy potatoes and the potatoes with sausage The pork chop was a bit disappointing  rather tough  but the accompanying fries were good We also had a salad but it must have been forgettable because I cant remember much about it except that it had too much mayonnaise in the dressing One of the best things was the wine  decent wines by the glass at very reasonable prices Just the thing to wash down the wonderful tapas

Author: gen p.
Content: First I do not understand the bad reviews for this place We go here at least once a month we have to because i always crave their food I dont understand also when people say go out to other restaurants chicago has so many good ones I tried to do that go to the better restaurants I always felt ripped off many times walking out hungry disappointed from lack of flavors and not so clean Iberico fulfills all my requirements for a restaurant Ill admit it is extremely loud but dont forget it is a younger crowd usually Everything is so clean from dishes glasses utensils and bathrooms Everything I had there is so flavorful and reasonably priced And since were such regulars there Ive noticed it is also consistent never disappointingJust went to yesterday to a restaurant that had almost 5 stars on yelp and couldnt find one flavorful thing that I can order again next time Also went to the signature room in january and 400 later everything was so blend Here I love everything from their saffron rice scallops to   goat cheese marinara ham wrapped dates quail paella grilled octopus  I never had such soft octopus anywhere I go a lot to tapas restaurant as I love tapas instead of just having a piece of fish or meat with 2 sides and by far this is the best Either you get the cold or hot tappas theyre all good Also Ive noticed everywhere that if you ask the waiter for recommendation and they say its good I take it if they say I havent tried it I learned not to order that Their desserts are really good too especially their specials if you get bored with the ones from the menu The restaurant I mentioned that had 5 starts here didnt have one decent desert choice Everyone in my family loves this place and I am having my sons graduation here Again it is a young crowd and kinda loud especially weekends but that doesnt stop me from going there to enjoy my dinners Theyre open for lunch too

Author: Dib D.
Content: Busy place Nice atmosphere One guy took our order then we never saw him again 3 others guys brought us our food and then we had to ask another waiter for our check The beef skewer and mushroom tapas were good The paella was a different story very dry Rice tasted like the 90 second uncle bens microwavable spanish rice

Author: Ro A.
Content: The tapas are ridiculously cheap but really good I love the white sangria and you can get a half pint for practically nothing Its loud and crowded but all worth it

Author: Sunny R.
Content: This is such a fun spot for groups and has the best tapas in the city It almost makes coming home from the most wonderful trip to Spain bearable Almost

Author: stephanie m.
Content: i dont eat a lot of nonamerican food but this place is great ive been here a few times and although its always packed its never disappointed

Author: allison k.
Content: I used to love this place 510 years ago They were the best tapas place in town However they renovated and got rid of a lot of the old charm that I loved They also got rid of the bacon wrapped dates How could you have a menu without bacon wrapped dates I have to be honest and say I havent been back in over a year now so maybe  theyve put them back on the menu

Author: Julia B.
Content: Second favorite Tapas place other than Cafe BaBaReeba I thought everything tasted awesome The different sangria was very tasty toothey have white peach ect The Cafe fills up very fast so make sure you grab a table fast The atmosphere is very Spanish

Author: Mariella C.
Content: this place is good they have a wide variety of tapas available and really reasonable prices and their sangria remains the best in town try their white sangria people are always going for tradition but their white is delicious and refreshing as well for tapas their queso de cabra and croquetas are to die for and the seafood is always good it just has become so popular that it is SO loud in here i went out with a friend and we had to scream in each others ears on top of the people talking they have music as loud as a club in here so not very intimate especially when youre two inches away from the next table but definitely a nice first stop of the night

Author: Alison T.
Content: There wasnt anything bad about this place  just not anything good to make me recommend it  Yes the food was cheap but you definitely get what you pay for One Spanish sausage dish could easily have come out of a can Id rather pay a little more for better food Service was fine given how incredibly packed it was  Waiter did forget one dish but also didnt charge us for it  Wait was only 15 minutes which I was surprised by given how other reviews read

Author: Liz F.
Content: I love Cafe Iberico  The goat cheese in tomato sauce is delish and their sangria is the yardstick by which I measure all other sangrias  I have loved everything Ive had here wellthe blood sausages were a little weird

Author: Calvin K.
Content: Ok I know everyone is different and all blah blah blah but please trust me on this restaurant dont knock it till you try it This is a great place to go before hitting the clubs or on second thought Iberico is great at anytime Picture a crowded night club with peeps dressed in high fashion now picture that scene with muy deliciosio comida y sangria  this is Cafe Iberico  The food is fantastic and I have been there over 25 times once or twice a week since I have discovered it and NEVER had a problem  Some may complain about the wait or servers come on cut them some slack Sure they may have a mishap here and there but they are human and EXTREMELY busy Go there enough put on a smile and your servers and bartenders will not forget you  Ive eaten all around Chicago but this is by far one of my favorites cheap eats real people great atmosphere and delicious food equals a great time at Cafe Iberico

Author: J. Loren H.
Content: Food is great The banana dessert even though it looked like I was chowing down on a sautéed penis was AWESOME The server however was not good I realize I tend to rate places based on service and this is not only because I am a server but also because I believe that the most important part of your experience at a restaurant is the hospitality This man was quite rude Its my friends birthday She was told on the phone when she made the reservation that she would be given a free birthday dessert We brought to the servers named David M attention that it was put on the bill Instead of getting a manager he argued with my friend and said ask any server here we dont give stuff for free He then walked away and pointed at our table while laughing and telling his coworkers about our dessert bs He came back to the table about 8 minutes later to inform us that he charged 13200 on a card we asked to have charged only 3000 Pay attention I cant stand this crap He went back to void everything and start over and wound up charging the 3000 to the card TWICE We asked to speak to the manager and he asked for a credit card to fix the mistake We asked again for the manager and he asked again for the card The birthday girl then said heres an idea GO GET THE MANAGER He went and got the manager and he handled the situation Sort of He explained what happened which we already fricken knew He wound up taking 50 bucks off our bill after we had to ASK for some sort of resolution which after discount was still 30200 If youre spending that much money at a restaurant you damn well better get the best fricken service you have EVER gotten I was really disappointed If you love tapas or have been meaning to try it eat here and enjoy it Just dont expect great service The city and its restaurants need to hire NICE FRIENDLY ATTENTIVE staff Not all of you suck Just David M and some poo heads at the bagel

Author: Maria C.
Content: People really make this place seem so great when really theres better restaurants out there  The really good thing that I liked a lot was the White Sangria  There is no way that you can get 4 tapas and a pitcher for 25  Most of the tapas were 5 and the pitchers were like 15  Something like that    I had this chicken that looked like an egg roll w some white sauce which tasted like someone chewed it up and then formed it into an eggroll  Didnt like that too much kind of grossed me out a little bit  Then I tried the chicken meatballs which I actually liked  It came in a bed of rice  The one that I really liked was the sausages  I ate those in seconds  My friend had all kinds of dishes that I didnt try for the simple fact that I didnt care for the items such as shrimp and some spicy potatoes  ouch  He thought that they were really good  Overall I think Ill stay at the bar and just have some Sangria

Author: N K.
Content: Delicious Amazing drinks outstanding paella and definitely try the goat cheese

Author: Amy L.
Content: Holy shit This place is hugeand its busy but they do have enough vegetarian tapas to keep me happy They also have some good sangria plus everything is reasonably priced Yay

Author: Kat T.
Content: Always liked coming here but tonight Night change that Hate it when people say theres no wait less than 10min before you are physically there then all of a sudden theres a 15min wait as soon as u walk in And the 15min in reality is 3040min wait Dont lie to your customers It is not fn cool Our time waiting here couldve been spent somewhere else especially when people are hungry Again DO NOT SAY THERE IS NO WAIT WHEN THERE REALLY IS its been about 45min  we ate still waiting

Author: Mikey S.
Content: It was ok Ive had much better tapas for the same price The best part was the side dishs rice potatos etc They had good spices very flavorful but not to spicy However all of the meats were flavorless like they hadnt been seasoned at all which in my mind was the most important part of the meal The atmosphere was ok more like a bar than a restaurant It was very loud and we were crammed into a tiny table with low lighting On a side note the sangria was good

Author: Richard L.
Content: My friend and I went to this restaurant when we were in Chicago  It was her first experience with Spanish food  Being an early dinner the place was very quiet but it was not long until the noise level rose as the place began to fill  The nose level never got to loud  We ordered paella and appetizers all of which were very good  We also had some Cava

Author: Vytas M.
Content: I can not wait come back for another dinner in this place I love them Spanish cuisine and of course sangria is the best at Cafe Iberico

Author: Doug p.
Content: their sangria is worth going for by itself but on top of that the food is great and very reasonably priced

Author: mary b.
Content: this place is cheaper than babareebas which might be because they spend much less effort on the upkeep of the place its not so pretty or warm as babareebas but the food is just as good and the sangria may even be better definitely my second place spot for tapas yum

Author: Adrienne C.
Content: paella is WAY TOO SALTY and the tables are WAY TOO CLOSElike might as well be at the same table close the gazpacho had no vegetables at all though the soup base itself was good the small clams sautéed with shallots white wine and parsley were fine i wouldnt initiate going back

Author: Jennifer V.
Content: The tapas are delicious and theres a great variety It can get very crowded on the weekends though Last time we went there was an hour and a half wait for a table

Author: han l.
Content: this place is wonderful the wait is long though it took us about 45 minutes on a friday night but once we were seated the food arrived pretty quickly extremely reasonable price

Author: Maureen M.
Content: this place is the real thing the food is delicious the wine is well priced the noise is what you left home for beef brochettes w carmelized onions and fries are a must this is a perfect spot for a small group

Author: Nery E.
Content: best tapas place in chicago  hands down

Author: Heather R.
Content: Great place for groups and the prices are reasonable

Author: Julie L.
Content: I love this place  It is absolutely HUGE inside  It is great if you are with one person or 20  Very inexpensive tapas and wonderful pitchers of Sangria   Go already

Author: amanda b.
Content: This place is great So much better than Baba Riba Good price for good food and the Sangria is to die for Baba Ribas is watered down and for 1899 you dont want watered down Sangria

Author: Julie O.
Content: This is my favorite restaurant in Chicago It is the shit The service is so awesome the food is so awesome the sangria is so awesome and the atmosphere is so awesome Its just so much fun Ive never had a bad time there The goat cheese bread is the best and I also love the ensalada russa The tomato bread is good too They recently opened up another restaurant upstairs for even more room And its really pretty up thereopen air But I havent tried the food so I dont know

Author: Blah B.
Content: I use to love this place great food and sangria for super cheap but the food isnt the same 3 years ago I had my bday dinner there and there was ants crawling outta of every corner everywhere We brought it to the managers attention and its seamed like he wasnt havent such a great day because instead of being a bit more attentive considering some of my invites had gotten bitten by ants he was rude Anyways the sangria is still great but Im not crazy bout the food anymoreSo sad

Author: A J.
Content: The last time my wife and I came here was about 5 yrs ago Back then we would go often and blitz ourselves on tapas and sangria The only real complaint back then was how loud it would be because it would always be packed Last night was the first time going there since then and the changes were horribly unbelievable This place transformed into a dive We are living in the suburbs now and we decided that well chance more than just one glass of sangria The server would not upgrade our sangria glasses to a 12 pitcher and said hed have to void out the twoglass order So what were thinking theyre going to get more money Duh We just said whatever and took the glasses We took one sip and noticed immediately that they were watered down significantly When the server gave us the new plates from the adjacent table for our tapas we noticed that the plates were not cleaned thoroughly We felt debrisresidue on the underside and could see bits on the topside My wife and I started getting that What happened to this place look on our faces When the tapas did come it didnt taste flavorful nor did it look appealing To top it off one of the plates chorizo y morcillo wasnt cooked sufficiently and we contracted food poisoning We lived in the bathroom the next day wondering if this was enough to file a suit or notify IDPH IL Dept of Public Health Before were done w the tapas we asked the server for the check so we could just pay eat whats left and get the hell out of there A complaint to the management would not have been productive because it wasnt about the money The quality of the visit was horrible compared to then This place used to be the bomb and everyone in town knew it But after seeing some recent reviews Im not the only one who noticed that things were bad They must have gotten different chefs andor different management during the time What a shame Lost a oncegreat hangout We will never go back there and I recommend nobody else patrons the place If anyone actually does enjoy their visit they would have been blown away in a good sense back then

Author: Joan I.
Content: What is all the hype about Service severely lacked atmosphere was much more of a  fast food tapas joint than anything and the food was NOT THAT GOOD  Of the four dishes we ordered and we typically order much more than four at other tapas places only one was okay The others were odd tasting over cooked or just meh   For 8 or 9 a plate  that was very unfortunate We love Cafe Ba Ba Reeba and always wanted to try Cafe Iberico Well we tried it and were sticking with Cafe Ba Ba Reeba

Author: C M.
Content: Very very good food  I am not a huge tapas fan but these were hearty tapas portions and delicious    The mussels tapas were definitely a standout  As an aside maybe it was the tapas and main courses that we chose but I would describe the food here as comfort food lots of terrific saucesgravies but on the heavier side    It did get very very very loud at around 700 PM on a Friday night  I would go back in a heartbeat but definitely try and avoid the peak crowd times

Author: D C.
Content: Ate here for dinner late on a weekday evening Was a bit crowded and table space was sparse for a tapas place I agree with some reviewers in that some of the food was a bit bland The Jamon manchego and pan con tomate plate was great So was the chicken empanada The dates were ok but the rice they came with wasnt very good The tortilla espanola was averagedecent flavor but a little bland and refrigerated definitely prefer it room temperature or warm We got the vegetarian paella and it wasnt that goodvery bland with minimal saffron On the plus side the portion sizes were good and prices ok in the 712 range The small 12 paella was fairly decent sized Overall 3 stars for a couple of good plates a couple of mediocre plates and decent portions for the price

Author: Katie P.
Content: I spent a semester studying in Sevilla and fell in love with the Spanish culture The food here is pretty authentic  although their patatas bravas were a little disappointing and I enjoyed myself However I was expecting a more authentic atmosphere They played outdated American music and I was hoping to hear some flamenco or Spanish music I would go back because the food and service was good however it didnt quite live up to my expectations

Author: Tao Tao W.
Content: we tried the upstairs restaurant instead for the northern style of tapas it was ok but should have sticked with the southern style the prune wrapped with meat was really good as was  the white wine sangria

Author: Jimmy W.
Content: This place surprised me on two totally different levels On a quick little two day jaunt to Chicago recently just for the heck of it I had Cafe Iberico recommended to me by a friend who lived in Chicago for a few years Upon entering the ambience immediately made me feel like I was walking into a club  not at all what I was expecting but not bad I would not recommend this place to anybody looking for a quiet dinner where you can have a quiet conversation whatsoever but fortunately thats not what I came for at all The service was pretty good fairly attentive but not fantastic We sat down at the bar and had some Sangria HIGHLY recommended while we waited for a table They have a neat system of displaying names on screens throughout the bar area underneath delightfully eurotrashy music videos when tables are ready so you can just hang out and enjoy yourself and not have to listen for your name to be called or deal with one of those buzzing lighty uppy pager things We ordered 3 tapas and one paella with the tapas coming out at various times and the paella coming out at the end All of the food was absolutely delicious and after 2 halfpitchers of sangria and enough food for at least 3 people or two very hungry people our bill was still only in the 60 range How cool Overall I was pleasantly surprised with the ambience being as fun and eurotrashy as it was and with how inexpensive a bunch of really tasty food was Great for vegetarians and carnivores alike just make sure youre ready for some dancey music while you eat

Author: Michelle B.
Content: We had a huge group here a few weeks ago for my besties birthday  Usually they wont seat you until your entire party gets there but they were nice enough to get our tables together and seat us early  The food was terrific and the sangria was delish and refreshing  The service was Meh  Although they seated us early when we got up to our table we waited FOREVER for water and drinks  When they finally got to us to take our drink orders we were simple and just ordered a bunch of pitchers of sangria  Strangely the waitress tried down selling us  we ordered 4 pitches to start with and she said we should only get 2 Um ok We like our drinks so we stuck to the 4 pitchers and low and behold ordered even more as the night went on  After the rest of our party got there they got thru their hiccups and the rest of the night went smoothly  The food was delish and came out quickly  Out of the many many things that we tried a few that Ill make sure to get again Queso De Cabra patatas bravas the potato salad and the grilled shrimp and octopus both cooked well not rubbery   I was stuffed by the end of the meal  And to make up for the hiccups at the beginning of the night the waitress brought the birthday girl a tasty desert in the shape of a falic symbol hehe  Overall Ill definitely be back for more  The space is a bit tight and crowded We had a long table and it was hard to manuver in and out  But the food was great and the price even better

Author: Cherisse G.
Content: Two levels Very crowded waiting for our table while at the bar on the first floor It was a Friday night I felt bad for the people who did have tables by the bar because people were literally leaning against their food We were accommodated for a table I believe up to 18 as people strolled in throughout dinner I felt our waiter was more attentive to the large table of girls behind us of the same number of diners For some reason we kept getting double of one order and it gets kind of chaotic when the plates come out one at a time and they just place it where theres space rather than near the person who ordered it I had two dessert plates with coffee the caramelized banana and chocolate flan The chocolate flan tasted like chocolate pudding and both were large enough to share with someone else My friend had the paella which she let me try which was good It was very loud and the room upstairs was bright yellow eyedrops please The prices however were not bad but I guess Im just not a fan Service was lacking The funniest part was when the waiter brought out the caramelized bananas in the shape of a guys nether regions with the help of two scoops of ice cream and whipped cream for the birthday boys

Author: K B.
Content: This place doesnt have a great atmosphere for a date youre trying to impress but completely cool for a hang out Casual date is ok too People come here dressed up in the evenings on weekends because this is the spot to grab food before or after you hit a club The food is DELICIOUS

Author: Mindy W.
Content: Ive been going here for the past three years now and the food has never failed me The long wait however can be aggrevating because theres not a lot of space to stand around and everytime I just feel that Im blocking people by the door Pitchers of sangria couldnt be any cheaper and always makes my trip here worth it I always order the Patatas Alioli to start off with Basically its cold potatoes mixed with oil sour cream garlic and chives I highly recommend it if youre not crazy about watching your weight Their paella is to die for as well Im also a fan of their chicken skewer that comes with the Spanish rice and sour cream The chicken is a bit bland but the sauce makes up for it Their garlic prawns make a perfect savory dish People have mixed opinions about this place it seems Either youre a fan or youre not Some say its too greasy but I think it all depends on what you order I personally love it They offer good salads on the menu if youre concerned about the grease I typically dont order salads when I dine out but Ive tried a few here and honestly theyre pretty good There has never been a time where I went here and didnt leave without getting dessert Theyre ice cream wrapped with crepe drizzled with strawberry syrup is amazing Prices are resonably low even if youre on a budget Come here earlier during the day so you wont have to wait in line

Author: Brianna L.
Content: my family and i love the olive tapas esp the garlic we fight over it hahathe octopus and fries is probably the best one on the menu we also get one of the salads which is good because it hearts of palm and not many places serve it but as far as taste goes it really has none at all so we have to spice it with salt and pepper

Author: Bryan C.
Content: I always thought the rule was to never order off a menu with pictures of its food  This place is quite the exception kids  I couldnt have previously told you what authentic spanish food was but apparently its exactly what is served at Cafe Iberico  Some of the menu is hit or miss but its a huge menu  Everyone has their options and theres a lot to choose from  Make sure to get a pitcher of the Sangria of course  The restaurant was very busy and quite crowded but its large so we were seated relatively quickly maybe a 15 or 20 minute wait  I do believe I enjoyed the hot tapas rather than the cold but to each their own  The service was outstanding and the price is right  Plates come out as they are ready and you can order as you go  Some highlights were the pollo croquettes the potato salad the mushrooms and the baked goat cheese  One big downfall was the trio of gazpachos  Kinda gross but some people like obnoxiously flavored cold soups so do what you will  All in all its really quite a fun dining experience and I would recommend it to anyone looking for something different on a Saturday night

Author: Yaskara a.
Content: The food was terrible My husband and I had a Paella but was really small and zero sea food We went with a group and they refuse to bill us separately to charge us an extra 18 more for service Also the Salpicon de mariscos was terrible only onion and tomatoes and zero sea food againg They also pretended to charge us for jerez for the paellaThe waiter was also rude to us we had a terrible time there

Author: Ali O.
Content: I love this place I seriously could go here every week Haha actually during sometimes of the year I do go here every week The service is fast  the tapas choices are numerousI really cant say anything bad

Author: Nicole C.
Content: Went here for my birthday on a Tuesday so it wasnt too crowded  The Sangra was excellentthe best I have ever had  The best dish by far was the potatochicken puff followed a close second by the bread covered with veggies  We also got some sort of chicken skewer thing which was good goat cheese and basil bread also good and garlic shrimp the garlic was a bit heavy on this  The only negative of the night was that we ordered a mushroom dish never received it but also were not charged for it  It didnt really end up mattering anyways because we were so full  Also priced wellwe got a pitcher of Sangria and five dishes for under 50

Author: Jeff H.
Content: i am kinda conflicted  its above average food  large selection of tapas  Not quite the same thing you get in Spainbut not so bad for being in Chicago  very festiveheavy crowd good peoplewatching  but that comes with the negativestoo many people  you have to talk as loud as possible jsut to make out what the person sitting next to you is saying  that may be ok in a club but in a restaurantthat was really annoying  the waitstaff cant keep up with the number of customers  you have to wait a long time before you get the orders taken get extra plates get drinks filled get your check  I dont know maybe i am just too typeA about this

Author: Araceli R.
Content: i love this restaurant i definely  recomended  evreting we order was delicioso   cant wait to go back

Author: Tom T.
Content: Always busy and loud and thats what I like about this placeAlso lets dont forget about food and SangriaGood place to come in and start your nightEnjoyTry shrimp in garlic oilto die for

Author: Kim S.
Content: The service was AWFUL We had to ask for someone to please take our order after waiting for 20 minutes after we were rushed to sit downwhen we asked for anything it took FOREVER and it was so LOUD Servers and management have absolutely no people skills The food is OK nothing special This place is a major disappointment and I wouldnt recommend it to anyone dont waste your time or money HORRIBLE HORRIBLE HORRIBLE

Author: Jackie C.
Content: Not as good as it used to be Tapas is good not stellar but the service could use some help We had reservations on a Sunday evening at 5 for 7 people It was fairly busy but not slammed We were seated quickly and our order was taken and the sangria arrived quickly  Our first few plates of food were delivered to the table next to us who began to serve themselves and eat it before the waiter came back and with a brief sorry to the other table took the half eaten platter and put it on our table and walked away with no explanation Then the next few dishes were attempted to be served to 2 other tables near us and they kept saying it wasnt theirs and we kept trying to tell the servers it was ours The 2 servers carrying food then began to argue on the floor between our tables about the table numbering etc They took our food away back to the kitchen then a few minutes later redelivered the same plates back to us After we had finished eating and our table cleared we talked about what dishes had been skipped Of the about 12 or 13 we had ordered they forgot 3 We told our waitress after the table was cleared and as we were waiting for our bills about them and that we didnt want them now as we were all done  but would like them taken off the bill As we were waiting for the bill a food runner shows up with the 3 dishes She had put in an order for it after we told her they were missing and we didnt want them We tried to send him away as we didnt want them now and of course we had no plates or silverware He wouldnt take them and then the waitress came back insisting we take them Finally we just said fine whatever and they left them and came back a few minutes later with silverware and plates Ive been there in the past and had great food and service This was my birthday dinner the company was lovely  the service less so

Author: Linda C.
Content: The food was delicious but Im still not convinced that what they are serving would be considered Spanish I went with a group of 9 on a friday night and the wait was about an hour Not too bad considering the amount of people that were crammed into this place Overall the food was tasty and the service was attentive I would recommend the octopus and fries the goat cheese the shrimp and the mushrooms

Author: Eric L.
Content: I went with a group of 8 for lunch on a Tuesday  We were promptly seated and given menus and the hungry bunch that we were we excitedly looked through our menus  However 20 minutes later nobody had come to our table to give us water or bread let alone take our order  I asked a waiter and he dismissively told me a waiter would be right with me  10 minutes later still nothing so i got another waiter who said he would talk with the manager  10 minutes later i had to stand up and chase down a waiter who finally got us some bread and water but didnt take our order  5 minutes later after further prompting a waitress came without even a sorry and took our order  We waited for about 45 minutes from when we seated until we were even able to order  After ordering the food came quickly and was good but not great and inexpensive  Im sure our experience isnt the usual but it was enough to keep most of us from making repeat visits  If you can overlook the service though the food is good and the prices are cheap

Author: Debbie H.
Content: I havent been to Cafe Iberico in years but decided to return after a friend mentioned hed never been and a Chicagoan for 20 years  I was in Mallorca last year and grew up dining at various tapas restaurants  While the atmosphere can be boisterous and awkwardly crowded I still think Iberico has the best tapas in this town  The sangria is nothing short of delicious  more burgandy than fruity more robust than sickly sweet  Since Ive been there last theyve extended their restaurant downstairs  When we arrived we were told it would be a 45 minute to an hour wait  Who cares  Red sangria was on the menuand servers came down to the bar about 30 minutes later with some passed snacks which was a nice and new touch  Fave tapas include the goat cheese in tomatos basil sauces gambas al ajilo tortilla the staple you can usually measure one tapas place to the next and the chicken croquettes  Muy bien Iberico

Author: Jill and Ying J.
Content: Two words cheap sangria  This review could end here and it would perfectly describe Cafe Iberico  The food is delicious and authentic  Best of all its cheap  Plates come in 37 arrangements and serving size is great for 2 people to share  The sangria which comes in either red or white wine versions is delicious and a wonderful way to start the evening  And like the food its also cheap  What really makes Cafe Iberico a place we keep coming back to is the feel that youre in a casual familyrun restaurant in Spain eating tapas  If youre looking to impress on a first date or impress a business client this would obviously not be the place  But just as Cafe Iberico makes you feel comfortable and at home this is the perfect place for your friends and significant other people who make you feel comfortably at home This is one of the few places in Chicago where we return to with some regularity because their weekly specials eg rabbit stew are continuously changing and ALWAYS fantastic and their classics are always as good as we remember them Must haves include but not limited to queso de cabra Baked goat cheese with fresh tomato basil sauce croquetas de pollo chicken croquettes with aioli sauce paella lomo de buey a la brasa beef tenderloin with potatoes almejas en salsa verde clams with shallots and white wine And dont forget the sangria

Author: Judy L.
Content: Hands down my favorite tapas restaurant in all of Chicagoand others may agree too with the long lines on weekends and nights so be prepared to wait for at least an hour The restaurant doesnt take reservations but offers stellar white and red sangria to keep you occupied while waiting for a table The sangria arent watered down with a pound of ice compared to other places Ive been to and they have a decent wine selection as well The decor is funky because the restaurant is divided into 4 sections each with its own theme Service is great and I applaud them for their work because it can be a madhouse at times with all the people standing around at the bar and loud conversations coming from all sides Both their hot and cold tapas are of good quality namely bacon wrapped dates mussels goat cheese and grilled octopus As with most paellas it takes around 20 minutes so order it right when you are seated if you are interested My favorite has always been the seafood paella very generous chunks of seafood provided Top off the night with some flan and coffee and youll leave with a contented smile on your face

Author: Matt P.
Content: The tapas here are pretty good but the NOISE level and the rude service took away from the experience  I had a friend visiting from out of town and I gave him the option to pick from a few tapas restaurants  We decided to venture downtown and go to Iberico  Be forewarned this restaurant has low ceilings tiled floors and its quite large therefore the noise level even when its only halffull is nearly deafening  My friend and I were literally screaming across the table at each other to be heard  Im all for lively places but this was to the point that conversation was difficult  Then the waiter we had clearly wanted to be anywhere but working at this restaurant  Even when visually trying to flag him down it was impossible to get him to come over and when he did notice us he was clearly annoyed  The tapas and sangria were pretty good but I know several other tapas options in the city that are just as good but you can actually hear the people in your party and service is consistently friendly  Oh yea the wait at Iberico can get to be a bit much too during peak periods

Author: David Z.
Content: We love this place Visit every chance we get Today I had a trio of Gaspacho soups beat garlic and tomato roasted peppers with quail breasts and eggs and a Spanish baked cheesecake  All were served cold Temperanillo wine Every choice we make is a new adventure Friday nights are LOUD We always find a parking place in the front for 3 at the meter Cant beat it for foodie cravings and European style

Author: Brian K.
Content: I used to go to Cafe Iberico at least twice a month and always had a great time  Then for whatever reason I stopped going there for a couple of years  When I returned I thought everything was a bit off the quality of food had gone down and the prices had gone up so I didnt go back until todayLet me first say I love good tapas go I to several other tapas places in Chicago and Ive been to Spain a few times and eaten lots of tapas  All that being said what a disappointment  Yes the sangria was good and if I was looking to get loaded at lunch this wouldnt be a bad choice  The place was busy but oddly quiet no music just TVs showing Spanish football  The tapas were just plain disappointing  The olives tasted strange and were mushy  The jamon platter was odd the toast was soggy there was a thick coating of chopped tomato on it and included one slice of jamon Iberico  The shrimp was fine but bland  The queso de cabra again came with soggy bread which used to be toast rounds  Finally the mushrooms which turn my wife into someone who would eat mushrooms were sad  They used to use small button mushrooms and caramelize them these where large mushrooms of varying types and Im not sure how they were cooked but I didnt care for themIm so bummed because I was really hoping Care Iberico would deliver but it didnt

Author: erika s.
Content: i already liked this restaurant a lotbeen here several times over the years i went the other night though and was pleasantly surprised to find that 3 weeks ago they introduced a new concept to the restaurant now on top of all their regular tapas they offer smaller portion tapas when you enter the restaurant it looks sort of like a sushi bar they have 50 different small plates that you can order by number the plates are perfect for 2 people to share and allow you to taste a great deal more things than the other size the best part each dish is between two and three dollars thank you cafe ibericothis is now officially my new fave place to go out on a budget

Author: Chad W.
Content: Great small plates Best octopus Ive had not chewy at all Good sausage the goat cheese in the red sauce was a nice treat the paella was sweeter than I like and the creme brule like dessert was good

Author: Michelle B.
Content: I tried this place after trying many of the other delicious tapas restaurants throughout the city and this place was a disappointment  Our wait staff didnt come around enough so our food got cold and the items we ordered were anything but fresh and had to be sent back  I wouldnt even consider me a picky eater but we will definitely not be visiting this place again

Author: Alisa N.
Content: I LOVE LOVE LOVE this place  It is a true happening city restaurant that attracts every kind of person you can think ofand they all want one thingSANGRIA  There are tons of people trying to crowd into Cafe Iberico on the weekends and somehow everyone gets seated pretty fast  The waiters are amazingI dont know how they keep all the orders straight  I love the grilled octopus the goat cheese and the saffron scallops  Although everything else is delicious as well  If you are trying to avoid the crowds on the weekend go for lunch on Sunday  Will be back over and over again

Author: rachel c.
Content: Mmmm   all I have to say is that I would never expect whipped mayonnaise over potatoes patatas alioli to taste so good but it does This place is a great A fun environment Great food Would definitely come back

Author: Maricar A.
Content: I must say the food has improved over the years I havent been here for years and I was taken back It was like a completely new place The food was much tastier this time around and I really enjoyed all the dishes we ordered We came here for a friends birthday and we were stuffed by the time we all got out of there Will be going back for sure and try the goat cheese Im not a big cheese eater but this one definitely hit on the spot

Author: Lindsay S.
Content: I have been here twice  and yes the sangria is great but the food is not The first time I went for dinner and we ordered a bunch of plates and they were all unmemorable  Not to mention that our last plate was brought out after we had paid and were about to get up to leave I had a feeling something was missing so instead of asking if we still wanted it the food was instead brought out with to go bags like I want to bring home goat cheese crostinis home NO The second time I went my friend asked me there for lunch and I reluctantly went and honestly the only thing that stands out from that meal was this hotdog looking thing that  had a mushy texture and I dont like that and the scallops which were actually good  The last thing that I have to say is when I went for lunch the place was empty like two or three tables in the middle were full and then one table by the window with two men and if you have been there you know the dining area is huge so we get sat right by these two men who are trying to negotiate with the manager the whole time about a catering order and the price and if they will or will not deliver to the location and which food they would be able to order and on and on and on and on and 40 min later they didnt even order anything and I am pretty sure they went there for free samples or something I feel like why couldnt we have been sat a table over bc it was empty This is a case where the place is busy because of the location

Author: dia m.
Content: I use to come here a lot in the past   I went last week with a few friends and my inlaws The overall experience was disappointing  The only good thing was the sangria  They didnt give us bread until about and hour of us being seated  No olive oil  I asked for butter for my mom and they brought back a huge cold  rock hard pat  They forgot to bring out dishes we ordered  I felt like we were waited on by bus boys  The fries with all the dishes were limp and tasted old  Patatas brava was awful not warm too salty just a messyuk shrimp not tasty  The food seem to lack flavor and the service lacked concern

Author: M T.
Content: Cool atmosphere but food was very bland  I love Spanish food so I was excited to get the paella but it was horrible the rice wasnt cooked right you couldnt even taste any saffron some of the seafood was burnt and the veggies were clearly from a frozen bag  The other dishes were pretty bad too  Spicy potatoes were ok but nothing like Spain   Service was good

Author: Eric L.
Content: This place gets great reviews  Ive only been here once but the service was horrible and the food was very average  I dont remember anything that I really liked  Thought the paella was pretty nasty

Author: Kendra M.
Content: While the service was fine I left very confused about what I had just experienced  Every time someone wants to go for tapas Cafe Iberico is always mentioned  I finally went for it and left wondering how this place keeps getting such good reviews  Every tapas I tasted was lacking flavor except for olive oil  I left the meal still hungry not because the portions were too small but I didnt find one tapas that was worth diving into

Author: Jim E.
Content: Great Tapas Loved the food here Make sure to try the white sangria

Author: Jeremy D.
Content: I used to go to Iberico with friends during college all the time  It is the perfect place to go with big groups looking for a fun night on the town  I recently returned and it was everything I remembered  The sangria here is so good that I dont mind having to wait for a table  I think it is fair to say Iberico serves up the best tapas in Chicago  I LOVE the goat cheese spicy potatoes octopus chorizo and the poached pears  It can get kind of loud but this is a place with a lot of energy and that makes it one of the most fun spots in the city  Viva Espana

Author: Celine K.
Content: Came here for dinner with my boyfriend  I have to say that I was very disappointed with the quality of the food  We ordered the ternera asada champinones a la plancha and gambas al ajillo  All the dishes were mediocre bland and definitely not authentic Spanish fare  The portions were very generous but the food was definitely not good  Quantity did not make up for quality

Author: E S.
Content: I definitely think this place can be a hit or miss on on certain days but on the majority of days  it is a hit I totally enjoy the patatas bravas croquetas the pollo queso de cabra and all their tasty seafood plates Im definitely a regular at this place

Author: Jim K.
Content: My favorite tapas place in the entire city They also have the best sangria of anywhere ive ever had i love wine and am an avid wine drinker but most sangrias try to blend too much wine and too much fruit and it just tastes well odd Somehow Iberico does it right My favorite dish isnt always on the menu but if you ask for it they can make it goat cheese stuffed dates wrapped in baconheavenly

Author: Jess K.
Content: if you became addicted to tortilla espanol delicious potato omelette while studying abroadspending time in Spain and the cravings have not subsisted this is the best place to get it in the city trust me on this plus in the deli section they have tortilla packaged in a togo containeri found the rest of the tapas here to be mediocre you could do better somewhere else in the city

Author: A. B.
Content: Best tapas in Chicago High quality food at VERY reasonable prices Pitchers of sangria are also a bargain compared to other tapas restaurants in the city Consistently an enjoyable dining experience

Author: Mark P.
Content: We sat in the bar area on a Saturday night It was crowded but thats what youre looking for and expect Most of the people in the bar area were Spanish which is a good sign Everything was very good but didnt quite wow me enough for five stars Would go back

Author: Erika S.
Content: Ive been going there off and on for 7 years now and I have noticed a decline in quality since its expansion This seems quite common in restaurants they become successful and then rely on their image rather than their food to sustain them Im not sure what it is exactly Perhaps its a change in ingredients I dont know Ive also lived in Spain and some of the dishes dont really live up to their name here The paella is ok for example I will have to say however that the goat cheese and pincho de pollo are excellent Also the hostess was incredibly rude to me last time and that left a bad taste in my mouth

Author: Emre C.
Content: This restaurant is super Its close to my university Roosevelt All students at Roosevelt should go there Its good place for drinks and food They have appetizer like food but they give lots like Turkish meze But dont go upstairs the new restaurant is not so good downstairs is more better

Author: Lauren B.
Content: Very reasonable Recommend the baked goat cheese in tomato sauce mushrooms squid and seafood paellaAttentive wait staff and food was brought out very fast

Author: Emily C.
Content: By far the BEST Tapas in Chicago SO authentic  After having lived in Spain Iberico makes you feel like you are there  Sangria Croquetas pisto y tortilla por favor  Only con is that there can be really long waits and no reservations last time I checked But then again thats pretty authentic too

Author: L V.
Content: The sangria is great The paella we had was wonderful also We had several selections of tapas and we liked everything we had It was a bit noisy so maybe not the best for a quiet evening But very lively for group dinners

Author: Acnalb M.
Content: Delicious authentic Spanish tapas My mom is from Madrid and loves going here whenever she is in town I recommend the Spanish tortilla Morcilla Gambas al ajillo and be the Sangria is delicious

Author: Julie C.
Content: I was amazed at how much food they give per plate Im so used to ordering 810 plates when I go for tapas but the kind waiter stopped us after four saying it was going to be too much for two people He was so right All of the dishes were great but I definitely recommend the red wine sangria and the paella iberica Overall perfect

Author: Shajan K.
Content: Ive been going to Cafe Iberico for about 12 years and always have had a good experience The ambiance and food are great The red sangria has lost its flare over the years but still good IBERICO FAVs PATATAS ALIOLI GARLIC POTATOES SALPICON DE MARISCO SEAFOOD SALAD PINCHO DE SOLOMILLO BEEF SKEWERS QUESO DE CABRA GOAT CHEESE WITH MARINARA SAUCE GAMBAS AL AJILLO GARLIC SHRIMP and MEJILLONES A LA MARINERA MUSSELS I will say the only thing that I dont like about the restaurant is the inability to make reservations especially when you have larger parties

Author: Fahad A.
Content: Really good food But really crowded and LOUD

Author: Erin M.
Content: I used to be a diehard fan of Iberico I pretty much refused to eat tapas anywhere else because Iberico was always better WAS I am so saddened by how much the quality of their food has gone downhill in the last year or two I used to love the queso de cabra goat cheese in tomato the pulpa octopus the patatas bravas or ali oli And the quality of all have appreciably declined It pains me to say it but I wont be visiting Iberico anymore

Author: Dave M.
Content: I have been here a few times and every time I go I have a good experience  It takes a long time to be seated on weekends but its worth it  Their sangria is good and not to expensive especially if you buy a small pitcher rather than by the glass  Tapas places are always fun to go to because you get to try so many different dishes  Food comes out very fast after you order and is very good

Author: Rose C.
Content: Just had lunch with 60 people at Cafe Iberico the food was terrific and the service fantastic  We had 9 different things from a package menu and 4 different desserts I had favorites the seafood salad and the pulpo oh and the garlic potato salad but every dish was delicious  I think no one will eat for the next week and still there was food left over to take home  Lots of the people there had never had tapas so that was fun for them and another large group were Spanish or had lived in Spain everyone was equally delighted with the food  I cant thank the chefs servers and manager enough it was seamless A wonderful really fun experience and I would gladly go to another event at Cafe Iberico

Author: Gaurav M.
Content: Good food and ambience

Author: Razzina z.
Content: One of my favorite low key places in Chicago  I always go there for a start of girls night out  Very reasonably priced great food great Sangria

Author: Tiffany G.
Content: This was my 1st tapas restaurant and I enjoyed so much I went back several times and visited a few others The ambiance in the restaurant is dark and although Im sure its meant to be romantic or set a tone it just comes off as dark You cant really be that romantic in such a large crowded restaurant Ive gone several times and enjoyed the food on all occasions We had a beef tip tapas with carmelized onions garlic potatoes and beef with goat cheese The meat was cooked to perfection and everything was seasoned well I must admit that every time Ive gone to this restaurant its been packed to capacity and its a long wait While this is great for buisness it can be a bother for patrons attempting to grab a quick bite If you go to this restaurant on the weekend you should definitely expect to be seated no  sooner than 45 minutes after arriving

Author: Jon R.
Content: wide tapas selection  cold beers the joint is packed on fridays and saturdays so expect the noise level to be high parking could be challenging too

Author: Yolanda D.
Content: I LOVE THIS PLACE Even though the last time I went the server was less than stellar  The sangrias are great The mussels are AMAZING I cant wait to go back

Author: Jessica P.
Content: meh Tapas Valencia or ba ba reba are much better dont waste your time or money Both of my other tapas restaurant that I recommend are better and cheaper We gladly gave our leftovers to a homeless man  Im just saying And after going to Spain we have recognized the very obvious differences Just because Cafe Ibgross was in a trendy neighborhood does not mean it is any good butgood serviceso pay for that

Author: Evan M.
Content: Horrible service  They dont care about satisfying customers anymore because they have so many so the servers are horrible

Author: Arthur O.
Content: I had a horrible experience just waiting for a table yesterday August 17th One of the front hostesses was rude to me within 5 minutes of my arrival I let them know that they have lost my business not only now but in the future I went to Cafe Ba Ba Ree Ba instead and had a wonderful meal along with wonderful service

Author: Tim K.
Content: This is one of the places I always visit when Im in Chicago It had been a few years since my last visit and they have changed some things There is now an actual tapas bar in the front of the restaurant where patrons can select the number of their item and have it delivered to the table Meanwhile you still get a menu and can order items off the menu as well I went with a group of four and two went to the front to order while I ordered items off the menu Needless to say we got a few too many items That would be a bad thing if everything was not out of this world delicious Hands down the best items we ordered were the pulpo a la plancha grilled octopus fried mussels served on a half shell the tortilla espanola and the garlic potatoes We ordered too many items to list here but there was not a dud with any of them Washed it all down with pitchers of white and red sangria Total came to 40 per person with generous tip Highly recommend and definitely will be back next time Im in Chicago

Author: mike s.
Content: Food is good great value cheap and tasty sangria pitchers enjoyed the scallops Interior atmosphere is just ok

Author: kristi p.
Content: best sangria ive ever had  food is delicious get ready to pig out  atmosphere is funky cool plenty of cold and hot tapas to choose from go there and let your hair down party party party

Author: Henry F.
Content: WAY THE HELL TOO NOISY  My wife and I have been to Iberico several times over several years and visited recently on a weekend night with two relatives from abroad  Their tapas and the prices were both OK but Id forgotten or finally appreciated what a horribly noisy place this can be  We were first seated in their northerly room well before it was full could not converse with one another due to the loud young customers blabbing over the overly loud Flamenco music and asked to be moved  We wound up in the southerly room downstairs as I recall and as it filled it became noisier than the other  The whole joint had nothing but the hardest of surfaces tile floors etc and not an ounce of soundabsorptive materials  Our entire evening was spent yelling at one another gesturing and asking for repeats   It must be the loudest restaurant in Chicago  Avoid this poorly planned hellhole if you value your hearing

Author: M R.
Content: been here a few times  great food great atmosphere

Author: Kara M.
Content: you know how you go to tapas places and people just start ordering and you kind of have no idea what the hell youre eating because youre like 3 glasses into the sangria and plates are flying by you at the speed of lightyeah so thats how cafe iberico was for me however i do remember a goat cheese and toasted bread dish some potatoes in a red sauce chicken skewers and a pear dish and that they were pretty good im one of those people who likes tapas but have a fave place to which no other tapas spot can hold a light to  PAZO IN BALTIMORE the food was good but there was no dish that completely wowed me which i had hoped for when we picked this place i have to say that the service was great and the waiter was attentive as we were ordering quickly and often i thought the prices werent too bad and there was a good serving of food with each plate this place is a def 35dammit yelp for not having a half starsheesh

Author: CE C.
Content: I think one of the reasons I love this place is for nostalgic reasons  I first went to this restaurant about 10 years ago and loved it than and keeping coming back everytime i visit chicago  Its also so impressive how well they have done for themselves and the expansion that occurred with this place  Even when tapas are so popular now which means more expensive they still only charge 4 for a glass of sangria  For dinner we had the tortilla espanola croquetas de pollo jamon iberico which were excellent probably the best parts of the meal  They just do the simple stuff so well nothing fancy about it just basic spanish tapas no crazy spin on it  The seafood salad was also excellent not fishy smelling at all  Also had the pincho de solomillo which we could have done without yes the meat was tender however the fries were absolutely unnecessary and tasted like they have been sitting out for days  The grilled calamari and stuffed chipirones served in squid ink was also delicious  The baked goat cheeseThe gambas al ajillo were not garlicky enough  Lastly we had the paella iberico which was disappointing  Although they say it takes 40 mins to cook where was that crusty rice bottom  Nevertheless we will return next time we are in chicago

Author: M R.
Content: authentic tapas from espana are challenging to find in the states  what made my night fun here was our food great service  reasonably priced tapas  i heart cafe ibericolo sientome gusta cafe iberico

Author: R E.
Content: When it comes to my favorite Tapas place in ALL of chicago Cafe Iberico is the place  Ive been coming here for years and it has never let me down  The place gets very crowded and although bumping up against other people can be a little uncomfortable at times it is worth the wait in my opinion  I wouldnt recommend coming if youre starving and want to be seated quickly  Come here knowing that youll have to wait possibly 3040 minutes and during that time relax and enjoy their Sangria  The food is delicious and reasonably priced in comparison to any other Tapas restaurants  The service has always been great and Ive never had a complaint  I have brought friends and family visiting from out of town and even my 70 year old mother who doesnt get out often and EVERYONE has thoroughly enjoyed their food and experience here  I always hesitate trying other Spanish Tapas Restaurants and honestly THEY NEVER MEASURE UP to Cafe Iberico  Bravo

Author: s s.
Content: We have been fans and frequent customers of Cafe Iberico since weve been in the city years  literally and were excited for the opportunity to have an event there on a larger scale  We held our wedding reception on the 2nd floor of Cafe Iberico this past May and worked with Karolina their private events coordinator on everything from the food to the decoration   Karolina was extremely accommodating and always made herself available to answer my many questions via phone and email  She was able to work with my many requests including space for a band dance floor photobooth dessert table etc and the end result was an awesome party in one of our favorite restaurants in the city  And the food  OMG  Really   We basically always have a good experience there on the many dinners weve had either on our own or with friends  But generally since its not a chain restaurant the food will always have a tiny bit of difference from night to night depending on who is making it We were amazed  The pulpo  patatas  gambas  every item we ordered for the wedding was something that we had ordered before and we absolutely could tell that they stepped it up a couple notches just for us Chef himself must have been in the kitchen overseeing the event from top to bottom because the quality that day was impeccable  It was amazing and hands down the best meal we had there by far  My only regret was that our stomachs were too small to try all of the food we ordered but our guests assured us that everything was a perfect 10   Thank you Chef Karolina and crew

Author: Lea G.
Content: terrible place they are serving you the small tapas that seat for hours in the display and on top of it they microwave them THAT IS TOTALLY GROSS

Author: Jane M.
Content: yeahIm a fan  fabulous food great atmosphere reasonable prices  go with a group and have a great time
